29template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
30class EXPORT_TEMPLATE_DECLARE(V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE) Dictionary
31 : public HashTable<Derived, Shape> {
32 using DerivedHashTable = HashTable<Derived, Shape>;
33
34 public:
35 using TodoShape = Shape;
36 using Key = typename TodoShape::Key;
37 inline Tagged<Object> ValueAt(InternalIndex entry);
38 inline Tagged<Object> ValueAt(PtrComprCageBase cage_base,
39 InternalIndex entry);
40 inline Tagged<Object> ValueAt(InternalIndex entry, SeqCstAccessTag);
41 inline Tagged<Object> ValueAt(PtrComprCageBase cage_base, InternalIndex entry,
42 SeqCstAccessTag);
43 // Returns {} if we would be reading out of the bounds of the object.
44 inline base::Optional<Tagged<Object>> TryValueAt(InternalIndex entry);
45
46 // Set the value for entry.
47 inline void ValueAtPut(InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> value);
48 inline void ValueAtPut(InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> value,
49 SeqCstAccessTag);
50
51 // Swap the value for the entry.
52 inline Tagged<Object> ValueAtSwap(InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> value,
53 SeqCstAccessTag);
54
55 // Compare and swap the value for the entry.
56 inline Tagged<Object> ValueAtCompareAndSwap(InternalIndex entry,
57 Tagged<Object> expected,
58 Tagged<Object> value,
59 SeqCstAccessTag);
60
61 // Returns the property details for the property at entry.
62 inline PropertyDetails DetailsAt(InternalIndex entry);
63
64 // Set the details for entry.
65 inline void DetailsAtPut(InternalIndex entry, PropertyDetails value);
66
67 static const bool kIsOrderedDictionaryType = false;
68
69 // Delete a property from the dictionary.
70 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static Handle<Derived> DeleteEntry(
71 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary, InternalIndex entry);
72
73 // Attempt to shrink the dictionary after deletion of key.
74 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static inline Handle<Derived> Shrink(
75 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary) {
76 return DerivedHashTable::Shrink(isolate, dictionary);
77 }
78
79 int NumberOfEnumerableProperties();
80
81 // Returns the key (slow).
82 Tagged<Object> SlowReverseLookup(Tagged<Object> value);
83
84 inline void ClearEntry(InternalIndex entry);
85
86 // Sets the entry to (key, value) pair.
87 inline void SetEntry(InternalIndex entry, Tagged<Object> key,
88 Tagged<Object> value, PropertyDetails details);
89
90 // Garbage collection support.
91 inline ObjectSlot RawFieldOfValueAt(InternalIndex entry);
92
93 template <typename IsolateT, AllocationType key_allocation =
94 std::is_same<IsolateT, Isolate>::value
95 ? AllocationType::kYoung
96 : AllocationType::kOld>
97 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static Handle<Derived> Add(
98 IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
99 Handle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
100 InternalIndex* entry_out = nullptr);
101
102 // This method is only safe to use when it is guaranteed that the dictionary
103 // doesn't need to grow.
104 // The number of elements stored is not updated. Use
105 // |SetInitialNumberOfElements| to update the number in one go.
106 template <typename IsolateT, AllocationType key_allocation =
107 std::is_same<IsolateT, Isolate>::value
108 ? AllocationType::kYoung
109 : AllocationType::kOld>
110 static void UncheckedAdd(IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary,
111 Key key, Handle<Object> value,
112 PropertyDetails details);
113
114 static Handle<Derived> ShallowCopy(
115 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary,
116 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung);
117
118 protected:
119 // Generic at put operation.
120 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static Handle<Derived> AtPut(Isolate* isolate,
121 Handle<Derived> dictionary,
122 Key key,
123 Handle<Object> value,
124 PropertyDetails details);
125 static void UncheckedAtPut(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary,
126 Key key, Handle<Object> value,
127 PropertyDetails details);
128
129 OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(Dictionary, HashTable<Derived, TodoShape>);
130};

171template <typename Derived, typename Shape>
172class EXPORT_TEMPLATE_DECLARE(V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE) BaseNameDictionary
173 : public Dictionary<Derived, Shape> {

175

178 HashTableBase::kPrefixStartIndex;

180 static const int kEntryValueIndex = 1;
181

183 inline int Hash() const;
184
185 // Creates a new dictionary.
186 template <typename IsolateT>
187 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static Handle<Derived> New(
188 IsolateT* isolate, int at_least_space_for,
189 AllocationType allocation = AllocationType::kYoung,
190 MinimumCapacity capacity_option = USE_DEFAULT_MINIMUM_CAPACITY);
191
192 // Allocate the next enumeration index. Possibly updates all enumeration
193 // indices in the table.
194 static int NextEnumerationIndex(Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary);
195 // Accessors for next enumeration index.
196 inline int next_enumeration_index();
197 inline void set_next_enumeration_index(int index);
198
199 // Return the key indices sorted by its enumeration index.
200 static Handle<FixedArray> IterationIndices(Isolate* isolate,
201 Handle<Derived> dictionary);
202
203 template <typename IsolateT>
204 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static Handle<Derived> AddNoUpdateNextEnumerationIndex(
205 IsolateT* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
206 Handle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
207 InternalIndex* entry_out = nullptr);
208
209 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static Handle<Derived> Add(
210 Isolate* isolate, Handle<Derived> dictionary, Key key,
211 Handle<Object> value, PropertyDetails details,
212 InternalIndex* entry_out = nullptr);
213
214 // Exposed for NameDictionaryLookupForwardedString slow path for forwarded
215 // strings.
216 using Dictionary<Derived, Shape>::FindInsertionEntry;
217
218 OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(BaseNameDictionary, Dictionary<Derived, Shape>);
219};

384// NumberDictionary is used as elements backing store and provides a bitfield
385// and stores property details for every entry.
386class NumberDictionary
387 : public Dictionary<NumberDictionary, NumberDictionaryShape> {
388 public:
389 static inline Handle<Map> GetMap(ReadOnlyRoots roots);
390
391 DECL_CAST(NumberDictionary)
392 DECL_PRINTER(NumberDictionary)
393
394 // Type specific at put (default NONE attributes is used when adding).
395 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT static Handle<NumberDictionary> Set(
396 Isolate* isolate, Handle<NumberDictionary> dictionary, uint32_t key,
397 Handle<Object> value,
398 Handle<JSObject> dictionary_holder = Handle<JSObject>::null(),
399 PropertyDetails details = PropertyDetails::Empty());
400 // This method is only safe to use when it is guaranteed that the dictionary
401 // doesn't need to grow.
402 // The number of elements stored and the maximum index is not updated. Use
403 // |SetInitialNumberOfElements| and |UpdateMaxNumberKey| to update the number
404 // in one go.
405 static void UncheckedSet(Isolate* isolate,
406 Handle<NumberDictionary> dictionary, uint32_t key,
407 Handle<Object> value);
408
409 static const int kMaxNumberKeyIndex = kPrefixStartIndex;
410 void UpdateMaxNumberKey(uint32_t key, Handle<JSObject> dictionary_holder);
411
412 // Sorting support
413 void CopyValuesTo(Tagged<FixedArray> elements);
414
415 // If slow elements are required we will never go back to fast-case
416 // for the elements kept in this dictionary. We require slow
417 // elements if an element has been added at an index larger than
418 // kRequiresSlowElementsLimit or set_requires_slow_elements() has been called
419 // when defining a getter or setter with a number key.
420 inline bool requires_slow_elements();
421 inline void set_requires_slow_elements();
422
423 // Get the value of the max number key that has been added to this
424 // dictionary. max_number_key can only be called if
425 // requires_slow_elements returns false.
426 inline uint32_t max_number_key();
427
428 static const int kEntryValueIndex = 1;
429 static const int kEntryDetailsIndex = 2;
430
431 // Bit masks.
432 static const int kRequiresSlowElementsMask = 1;
433 static const int kRequiresSlowElementsTagSize = 1;
434 static const uint32_t kRequiresSlowElementsLimit = (1 << 29) - 1;
435
436 // JSObjects prefer dictionary elements if the dictionary saves this much
437 // memory compared to a fast elements backing store.
438 static const uint32_t kPreferFastElementsSizeFactor = 3;
439
440 OBJECT_CONSTRUCTORS(NumberDictionary,
441 Dictionary<NumberDictionary, NumberDictionaryShape>);
442};

444// The comparator is passed two indices |a| and |b|, and it returns < 0 when the
445// property at index |a| comes before the property at index |b| in the
446// enumeration order.
447template <typename Dictionary>
448struct EnumIndexComparator {
449 explicit EnumIndexComparator(Tagged<Dictionary> dict) : dict(dict) {}
450 bool operator()(Tagged_t a, Tagged_t b) {
451 PropertyDetails da(dict->DetailsAt(
452 InternalIndex(Tagged<Smi>(static_cast<Address>(a)).value())));
453 PropertyDetails db(dict->DetailsAt(
454 InternalIndex(Tagged<Smi>(static_cast<Address>(b)).value())));
455 return da.dictionary_index() < db.dictionary_index();
456 }
457 Tagged<Dictionary> dict;
458};
